On Wed, Jul 6, 2011 at 10:02 PM, Joe <spotop(-at-)gmail.com> wrote:
> Guys, if i remove the brake light switches on the booster, will fluid come
 out? Nothing is mentioned in the bentley or haynes about this. Joe

Yes. And you will have to bleed your brakes again.

Your brake lights are turned on by the hydraulic pressure acting on
the switches, somewhat like the oil pressure light.

John
